    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Zurich Zebras is anchored by a massive matchup advantage for **Yordan Alvarez** (82.97), who faces a favorable spot against Gil (xERA 5.74). With a strong plate-discipline profile and a significant bump from his #2 spot in the order, **Yordan Alvarez** is our clear ceiling play. Joining him at the top of the projected efficiency charts is **Junior Caminero** (71.00); despite a slight park penalty, his talent profile and #2 position against Woods Richardson make him a locked-in core piece for today\u2019s 5x5 run production. While we prioritize speed for our scarcity needs, the raw output projections for these two middle-order bats are simply too high to ignore.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Hyeseong Kim** (44.54) on the pine. **Hyeseong Kim** entered the calculation with legitimate appeal as a speed threat, but his poor platoon outlook against Imanaga, coupled with a deep lineup density, nudged him just below the threshold for our starting nine. Elsewhere, we are monitoring the risks associated with facing top-tier arms like Sale, who suppresses the ceilings of both **Trea Turner** (54.65) and **Kyle Schwarber** (52.96). While **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** remain in the lineup due to their elite plate-appearance consistency, their scores reflect the difficulty of the matchup. Similarly, **Victor Scott II** (53.24) is tasked with providing SB production against Hancock, though we caution that his low spot in the order slightly limits his base-run frequency.\n\nThe squad remains fully focused on optimizing our daily game caps, benching players like **Chase Meidroth** and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** to ensure we maintain flexibility for high-leverage days later in the week. We continue to track **Christian Yelich** on the IL, as his eventual return will significantly complicate our roster construction. For today, our strategy relies on **Yordan Alvarez** and **Junior Caminero** to provide the heavy lifting, while **Caleb Durbin**, **Josh Smith**, and **Victor Scott II** serve as the primary conduits for our stolen base objectives. Proceed with the current configuration as the daily efficiency scores favor this aggressive offensive stack.",
